Welcome to my first CLI project! I am new to linux and writing shell commands, so I will explain as if we are BOTH new to this experience. If you know what you're doing, feel free to ignore this OR message me on discord @oakienlookie so I can update this disclaimer. SO . . . 

Attached to this folder is the CLI named 8485. ADD THE 8485 FILE to your home folder (~)
then, open your terminal and run these 3 commands.

mkdir -p ~/.local/bin
mv 8485  ~/.local/bin/8485
chmod +x ~/.local/bin/8485

after this, you will be able to run (8485) commands and ENJOY!!

